@NODE startrange "Start-Ripp"

                        Main Window - Buttons Help

                                Start-range
                                ===========

Here you can write the range from where you want to start searching the 
memory..

@ENDNODE

@NODE stoprange "Stop-Ripp"

                        Main Window - Buttons Help

                                Stop-range
                                ==========

Here you can write the stop range where you want to stop searching the
memory..

@ENDNODE

@NODE player "ModulePlayer"

                        Main Window - Buttons Help

                               ModulePlayer
                               ============

This button will start EaglePlayer/DeliTracker for playing the module you
have found.. EaglePlayer is only working if the "Use Delitracker" feature
is turned off in the preferences (on/off tags).. If the "Use DeliTracker"
option is turned on, SR will use DeliTracker to play the found module..

@ENDNODE

@NODE find "Find"

                        Main Window - Buttons Help

                                   Find
                                   ====

This button will search the memory range for a given string, given by
you. This means that SR will search from START->STOP range you have
selected, or changed to.. 

@ENDNODE

@NODE write "Write"

                        Main Window - Buttons Help

                                   Write
                                   =====

This button will save the found module to your HD, or to your RAM disk..
Depends of what you have configured in the preferences.. It is
recommanded that you save things to your RAM disk, and then save them
to your HD if everything was okay when saving it.. 

@ENDNODE

@NODE read "Read"

                        Main Window - Buttons Help

                                   Read
                                   ====

This button will pop-up a file requester, asking you to select one or
more files, so that SR can hunt them for modules. 
@ENDNODE

@NODE diskread "DiskRead"

                        Main Window - Buttons Help

                                 DiskRead
                                 ========

This button will open a new window, where you can choose what DISK you want
to make a HARD-copy of. This will create an Imagefile on your RAM: HD: or 
Disk, depending of what you have configured in the preferences.. In other 
words, this button will just create an imagefile where you can search for
modules.

@ENDNODE

@NODE memdump "MemDump"

                        Main Window - Buttons Help

                                  MemDump
                                  =======

This button explains itself, just by looking at it.. Anyway; this will
open a new window where you can decide what part of the memory you
want to view.

@ENDNODE

@NODE clrmem "ClearMem"

                        Main Window - Buttons Help

                                 ClearMem
                                 ========

This button will clear the memory from trash, and no-used memory. It's more
like the Avail flush command, but this really clears the memory.. :)

@ENDNODE

@NODE about "About"

                        Main Window - Buttons Help

                                   About
                                   =====

Well, as it says.. This will just open a window where you can find some
information about the ripper itself.. Release date, supported formats
and so on.. The names of the formats aren't actually written here though,
just how many of them are included.. hehe.. 

@ENDNODE

@NODE memtype "MemTypes"

                        Main Window - Buttons Help

                                 MemTypes
                                 ========

With this cycle button, you can choose what kind of memory SR should be
searching from.. You can choose between: FastMem and ChipMem..

@ENDNODE

@NODE modstypes "ModsTypes"

                        Main Window - Buttons Help

                                 ModsTypes
                                 =========

With this cycle button, you can choose what type of searching you want
SR to do.. You got two options:

	- Multi search, will search the memory for ALL supported module
	  formats..
	- Single search, will specifically search for ONE of the supported
	  module formats..

@ENDNODE

@NODE hunt "Hunt"

                        Main Window - Buttons Help

                                   Hunt
                                   ====

Well, another self-explained button.. This will start the search process,
and see if SR can find any supported sound formats.. 

@ENDNODE

@NODE stophunt "StopHunt"

                        Main Window - Buttons Help

                                 StopHunt
                                 ========

Well, this button will just stop the hunt process.. 

@ENDNODE

@NODE continue "Continue"

                        Main Window - Buttons Help

                                 Continue
                                 ========

This button will continue the search from the last position it stopped..

@ENDNODE

@NODE samples "ModInfo"

                        Main Window - Buttons Help

                                  ModInfo
                                  =======

This button will be enabled if a module is found during the hunt process..
When you press this, another window will open where you can get some
information about the found module.. Not all formats are supported yet..

@ENDNODE

@NODE diskreadwnd "DiskRead"

                         * DiskRead Window Help *

		@{" Drives " link drive }
		@{" Stop " link dstop }
		@{" Start " link dstart }
@ENDNODE

@NODE drive "Drives"
                       Single Window - Buttons Help

                                  Drives
                                  ======

With this cycle button you can select the disk drive you want to read
from.. In the range of: DF0-DF4..

@ENDNODE

@NODE dstop "Stop"
                       Single Window - Buttons Help

                                   Stop
                                   ====

This button will stop the reading process, and will cancel the whole
operation..

@ENDNODE

@NODE dstart "Start"
                       Single Window - Buttons Help

                                   Start
                                   =====

This will start the reading process of the selected diskdrive, and create
a imagefile in your RAM:, HD: or the disk you have chosen to save it to..

@ENDNODE

@NODE memorydumpwnd "Memory Dump"

                        * MemoryDump Window Help *

		@{" Next " link next_adr }
		@{" Goto Address " link gotoaddr }
		@{" Prev " link prev_adr }
@ENDNODE

@NODE next_adr "Next"

                     Memorydump Window - Buttons Help

                                  Next
                                  ====

This will refresh the list, get the next memory blocks, and let you 
view them..

@ENDNODE

@NODE gotoaddr "Goto Address"

                     Memorydump Window - Buttons Help

                             Address location
                             ================

Here you can type in the address you want to have a look at, and
SR will do the rest...

@ENDNODE

@NODE prev_adr "Prev"

                     Memorydump Window - Buttons Help

                                 Previous
                                 ========

This will refresh the list, get the previous memory blocks, and let you
view them..

@ENDNODE

@NODE modfound "Module found..."

                      * "Module Found" Window Help *

		@{" Skip " link foundskip }
		@{" Write " link write2 }
		@{" View " link foundview }
@ENDNODE

@NODE foundskip "Skip"

                    Found Module Window - Buttons Help

                                   Skip
                                   ====

This button will just do the same stuff as the "Continue" button..

@ENDNODE

@NODE write2 "Write"

                    Found Module Window - Buttons Help

                                   Write
                                   =====

This button is the same as the "Write" button located on the main
SR window.. 

@ENDNODE

@NODE foundview "View"

                    Found Module Window - Buttons Help

                                   View
                                   ====

This button does the same as the "Memdump" button, except that it will
take you directly to the found location...

@ENDNODE

